# Add DATO_CMS_BASE_EDITING_URL and `datocms.baseEditingUrl`

Dastro 1.3.0 introduces visual editing support via DatoCMS content links. `DastroConfig.datocms.baseEditingUrl` is now a **required** field.

Three files need updating in the consuming project.

---

## 1. `.env.example` (and any real `.env`)

Add the new environment variable:

```
DATO_CMS_BASE_EDITING_URL=https://<your-project>.admin.datocms.com
```

Replace `<your-project>` with your DatoCMS project slug (the subdomain shown when logged in at `*.admin.datocms.com`).

---

## 2. `src/config/dastro.config.ts`

Import the new env var and wire it into the `datocms` section.

### Before

```ts
import {
  ALLOW_DATO_ENVIRONMENT_SWITCH,
  DATO_CMS_ENVIRONMENT,
  DATO_CMS_TOKEN,
  SIGNED_COOKIE_JWT_SECRET,
  SECRET_API_TOKEN,
  DEVELOPMENT_PREVENT_SEARCH_INDEXING,
  DEVELOPMENT_DEBUG_VIEW_ENABLED,
  APP_BASE_URL,
} from 'astro:env/server';

// ...

const dastroConfig: DastroConfig<Types> = {
  // ...
  datocms: {
    token: DATO_CMS_TOKEN,
    environment: DATO_CMS_ENVIRONMENT,
    allowEnvironmentSwitch: ALLOW_DATO_ENVIRONMENT_SWITCH,
  },
  // ...
};
```

### After

```ts
import {
  ALLOW_DATO_ENVIRONMENT_SWITCH,
  DATO_CMS_ENVIRONMENT,
  DATO_CMS_TOKEN,
  DATO_CMS_BASE_EDITING_URL,
  SIGNED_COOKIE_JWT_SECRET,
  SECRET_API_TOKEN,
  DEVELOPMENT_PREVENT_SEARCH_INDEXING,
  DEVELOPMENT_DEBUG_VIEW_ENABLED,
  APP_BASE_URL,
} from 'astro:env/server';

// ...

const dastroConfig: DastroConfig<Types> = {
  // ...
  datocms: {
    token: DATO_CMS_TOKEN,
    environment: DATO_CMS_ENVIRONMENT,
    allowEnvironmentSwitch: ALLOW_DATO_ENVIRONMENT_SWITCH,
    baseEditingUrl: DATO_CMS_BASE_EDITING_URL,
  },
  // ...
};
```

The `DATO_CMS_BASE_EDITING_URL` env field is declared by the dastro integration itself, so no changes to `astro.config.ts` are needed.

---

## 3. Netlify / CI

Set `DATO_CMS_BASE_EDITING_URL` in every deploy environment (Netlify UI, GitHub Actions secrets, etc.) before deploying — the schema is required and the build will fail otherwise.

---

